                        <interp inst="t18380917-name-439" type="surname" value="COOK"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18380917-name-439" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM COOK</persName>
                  </hi>. I am a glass—burner, and live in Drury—court, Drury-lane. The prisoner has been my apprentice nearly four years—he was articled for seven years—on the 6th of September I sent him to fetch half a hundred weight of plaster, and gave him half a crown to pay for it—it was to come to 2<hi rend="italic">s</hi>.—he did not return with the plaster or money—he was brought to me afterwards, and said he had spent the money.</p>
